<h3>3. Installation and Setup</h3>

<p>Install from the <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=org.futo.inputmethod.latin.playstore" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><strong>Google Play Store,</strong></a> <a href="https://app.futo.org/fdroid/repo/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><strong>F-Droid,</strong></a> or <a href="https://github.com/futo-org/android-keyboard/releases" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><strong>Github.</strong></a> Once installed, set FUTO Keyboard as your default Android keyboard.</p>

<h3>4. Features</h3>

<h4>4.1 Privacy Respecting</h4>

<p>FUTO Keyboard does not connect to the internet and does not request network privileges. Your keystrokes, inputs and voice data cannot be sent to any party. I verified this myself using GrapheneOS:</p>

<img src="/images/futokeyboardpermissions.jpg" alt="FUTO Keyboard permissions showing no network access" class="guide-img-narrow">

<h4>4.2 Everything you Need from a Keyboard App</h4>

<ul>
  <li>A wide variety of light and dark themes</li>
  <li>Full emoji support</li>
  <li>Clipboard manager</li>
  <li>Text prediction and swipe typing</li>
  <li>Multi-language support</li>
  <li>Voice to text support</li>
  <li>Support for imported voice to text models</li>
</ul>

