<h4>4.3 Source Code is Available and Verifiable</h4>

<p>The source code is available under FUTO's "source first" licensing standard. Code is publicly viewable and verifiable. How this differs from traditional open source is that it <a href="https://futo.org/about/futo-statement-on-opensource/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">"will not force programmers to let others, especially the tech oligopoly, profit from their work for free."</a></p>

<h4>4.4 Honor Based Payment</h4>

<p>Choosing not to pay will not impact your ability to use it. As put by Louis Rossman, using it without paying <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GYX92lLpZ20" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">"will be between you and your god."</a></p>

<h3>5. Final Remarks</h3>

<p>With essentially everything you do on an Android smartphone making use of the keyboard it is great to have the peace of mind that it does not connect to the internet. I don't trust Google, Samsung, Motorola or Huawei in the slightest and neither should you.</p>

<p>I would highly recommend FUTO's offer instead!</p>

